JOHANNESBURG – Demand for processed meat has declined by 75 percent following the deadly listeriosis outbreak. READ: Tiger Brands still destroying contaminated polony The Department of Trade and Industry (dti) said research shows the pork industry has been hardest hit. The demand for pork cold cuts dropped by 50 percent, with an estimated decline of 40 percent in profits. WATCH: Rate of listeriosis infections down The bacteria infected 1,038 people and killed 208. It was traced to ready-to-eat processed meat products. eNCA